transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Yes, I have a question. I just received another order from you, and I didn't order anything.

Speaker 2: Okay. Let me see what's going on.

Speaker 1: Yes, thank you.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: I guess this is some kind of auto program that you got me signed up for, but I don't have anything like that.

Speaker 2: If I want something, I place the order.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: If you have any auto program, you need to cancel it and return my money to this order.

Speaker 1: Okay. Mr. Jerry?

Speaker 2: Yes, right.

Speaker 1: Yes, I think what happened was the refill, but what I'm going to do, I'm going to pause your prescription because you don't need it as often.

Speaker 2: And just write refuse return to those PL, okay?

Speaker 1: And I'm starting the refund process, okay?

Speaker 2: Okay. What do you want me to do?

Speaker 1: Just put refuse return on the package. That's all.

Speaker 2: If you open it, tape it nicely in the back, put it back in your mailbox.

Speaker 1: When the mailman sees that, he's going to understand that's not for you.

Speaker 2: He's got to send that back to the source where it came from.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: I'll just open the top. I'll take it back.

Speaker 1: The driver didn't even know what it was, so I'll put it back in the mailbox.

Speaker 2: Yeah, do it nicely.

Speaker 1: And I'm pausing the prescription for you, okay?

Speaker 2: So that way you don't get it every month.

Speaker 1: They pause you up to half a year if you get it every month.

Speaker 2: No, I don't need any auto refill.

Speaker 1: Okay, so I'm going to cancel.

Speaker 2: Be aware of the price change, okay, when you reorder.

Speaker 1: Because I'm going to have to cancel the prescription they finance for you here.

Speaker 2: Because I'm not pausing you.

Speaker 1: So when they refinance that again,

Speaker 2: they got to apply that to the cost of your medication, okay?

Speaker 1: Yeah, okay. And so what's the amount of my refund on this?

Speaker 2: $113.95.

Speaker 1: Yeah, okay.

Speaker 2: All right, we'll go back in the mailbox, thank you.

Speaker 1: All right, and you want to cancel your prescription.

Speaker 2: You don't want to pause it, correct?

Speaker 1: I don't want anything if I called and ordered.

Speaker 2: So the only way, because I got to let you know that that's really important,

Speaker 1: the only way for you to maintain your price is to pause the prescription.

Speaker 2: As far as it goes, it's half a year, and then you get the refill.

Speaker 1: And then you get another refill half a year after that.

Speaker 2: That's the minimum.

Speaker 1: Now, if you cancel the prescription, which is fine, I don't mind doing that,

Speaker 2: the only difference, I got to let you know that,

Speaker 1: is that they're going to reinvest, get a new doctor evaluation.

Speaker 2: Because you're restarting over.

Speaker 1: That being said, price will be up.

Speaker 2: That's the only difference.

Speaker 1: Now it's up to you, whatever works best for you.

Speaker 2: I don't mind doing either or.

Speaker 1: I don't care if I cancel or I pause it.

Speaker 2: What do you mean?

Speaker 1: So when you cancel, you lose the prescription they finance.

Speaker 2: And every time they got to refinance your new doctor evaluation.

Speaker 1: Because they got to legally have a doctor evaluation.

Speaker 2: Okay, so why can't you just pause it, and if I want to order something, I'll pause it.

Speaker 1: Right, that's what I'm saying.

Speaker 2: That's why I offer to pause you so you can reorder.

Speaker 1: Yeah, well, just pause it.

Speaker 2: If I want something, I'll call you, but if I don't call you, don't send me nothing.

Speaker 1: So when you pause it, you get to refill half a year from now.

Speaker 2: Unless you call to change that refill.

Speaker 1: Let's say I put you off until July 21st.

Speaker 2: You can move that around, basically.

Speaker 1: But you got to have a date to lock the price in some way somehow.

Speaker 2: I don't care about the price as long as you don't send me anything unless I order it.

Speaker 1: Okay, if I don't order, don't send me anything.

Speaker 2: I'm going to have to cancel then.

Speaker 1: Okay, well, then cancel, whatever you have to do.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right, everything I've been canceled, like I said, be aware of price change, but you're all set, sir.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Everything canceled.

Speaker 2: Okay, bye.

Speaker 1: Just return that for the refund, okay?

Speaker 2: We're going to refund you, right?

Speaker 1: Refuse return on it, and we're going to refund you, and everything's canceled here.

Speaker 2: All right, you want me to try to return to sender right on the front label here?

Speaker 1: Yes, sir.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right, we'll do it.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: Do you need anything else?

Speaker 2: No, that's it.

Speaker 1: You're all set.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right, thank you.
